body:
This branch provides fused types. There are two non-serious failing tests in py3k which I will fix somewhere later this week or in the weekend when I have time.

This disables the caching of the cython scope, however, which may slow down cython.compile (it grossly messes up the test suite, I couldn't find a way to keep it in). 

I think we should fix this by compiling all cython utilities (and other C utilities with non-inline functions as well), and creating a libcython shared library. Common inline functions should end up in a header file that can be shared.
This could all be disabled in distutils and a cython command line option, which will mean you get the current behaviour (longer Cython and C compile times, larger executables).

We should also figure out a way to serialize Entry objects from CythonUtilities, which could easily and swiftly be loaded when creating the cython scope.

                     self.type = func_type.return_type

                 else:

                     self.type = PyrexTypes.error_type
 
+    def parse_indexed_fused_cdef(self, env):
+        """
+        Interpret fused_cdef_func[specific_type1, ...]
+
+        Note that if this method is called, we are an indexed cdef function
+        with fused argument types, and this IndexNode will be replaced by the
+        NameNode with specific entry just after analysis of expressions by
+        AnalyseExpressionsTransform.
+        """
+        self.type = PyrexTypes.error_type
+
+        self.is_fused_index = True
+
+        base_type = self.base.type
+        specific_types = []
+        positions = []
+
+        if self.index.is_name:
+            positions.append(self.index.pos)
+            specific_types.append(self.index.analyse_as_type(env))
+        elif isinstance(self.index, TupleNode):
+            for arg in self.index.args:
+                positions.append(arg.pos)
+                specific_type = arg.analyse_as_type(env)
+                specific_types.append(specific_type)
+        else:
+            specific_types = [False]
+
+        if not Utils.all(specific_types):
+            self.index.analyse_types(env)
+
+            if not self.base.entry.as_variable:
+                error(self.pos, "Can only index fused functions with types")
+            else:
+                # A cpdef function indexed with Python objects
+                self.base.entry = self.entry = self.base.entry.as_variable
+                self.base.type = self.type = self.entry.type
+
+                self.base.is_temp = True
+                self.is_temp = True
+
+                self.entry.used = True
+
+            self.is_fused_index = False
+            return
+
+        fused_types = base_type.get_fused_types()
+        if len(specific_types) > len(fused_types):
+            return error(self.pos, "Too many types specified")
+        elif len(specific_types) < len(fused_types):
+            t = fused_types[len(specific_types)]
+            return error(self.pos, "Not enough types specified to specialize "
+                                   "the function, %s is still fused" % t)
+
+        # See if our index types form valid specializations
+        for pos, specific_type, fused_type in zip(positions,
+                                                  specific_types,
+                                                  fused_types):
+            if not Utils.any([specific_type.same_as(t)
+                                  for t in fused_type.types]):
+                return error(pos, "Type not in fused type")
+
+            if specific_type is None or specific_type.is_error:
+                return
+
+        fused_to_specific = dict(zip(fused_types, specific_types))
+        type = base_type.specialize(fused_to_specific)
+
+        if type.is_fused:
+            # Only partially specific, this is invalid
+            error(self.pos,
+                  "Index operation makes function only partially specific")
+        else:
+            # Fully specific, find the signature with the specialized entry
+            for signature in self.base.type.get_all_specific_function_types():
+                if type.same_as(signature):
+                    self.type = signature
+
+                    if self.base.is_attribute:
+                        # Pretend to be a normal attribute, for cdef extension
+                        # methods
+                        self.entry = signature.entry
+                        self.is_attribute = True
+                        self.obj = self.base.obj
+
+                    self.type.entry.used = True
+                    self.base.type = signature
+                    self.base.entry = signature.entry
+
+                    break
+            else:
+                assert False

commit.message: Support for fused types in cdef functions
Fix error messages in ctypedefs
Disallow private types in public or api cdef functions
Fix compiler crash with type inferencing and add all() and any() to Utils
Support sharing of cdef functions with fused types
Allow type checks on fused types
Allow type expressions in comparisons
Fix cython.typeof() for fused types
Constant fold fused type check expressions with branch pruning
Disallow use of unspecialized fused types
Fix Python 3 compatibility
Update parsing.pxd
Fix a little bug
merge
Pass some more tests
Fix cython.typedef(cython.fused_type())
Remove manual branch pruning
Support casting and assignment of fused functions to specialized functions
Allow indexing of fused cdef functions
Change semantics of fused types
Support optional fused-typed arguments in cdef functions
Support fused cdef methods
Support fused cpdef functions with Python indexing
Runtime dispatch to specialized cpdef
Merge fused cdef functions with master
Fix some code style issues
Merge fixes from fused_cdef
Revert typeof() strings back to "list object" etc

Change fused types syntax:

    cdef fused my_fused_type:
        type1
        type2

and

    my_fused_type = cython.fused_type(type1, type2)

in pure mode.
merge
Pass failing tests and adapt for control flow
Support fused def functions + lambda + better runtime dispatch
merge -- working fused types, broken cython testscope
Fix cython scope caching (it breaks about half of the test suite, but it probably slow down cython.compile)
Fix build error
Remove unneeded code after merge
Fix error message in error test
Fix python 3 deepcopy & sorting compatiblity
Fix some style issues
Make NotConstant a singleton & fix 2 fused py3k tests
Omit fused function from module function table
Add documentation for fused types
Support fused memoryviews & fused base types, disable fused generators, disable memoryview pointer dtypes
Fix memoryview error test
Merge in fixes from master
PyUnicode_FromString macro for py < 2.6 & PyMemberDef flag

Merge branch 'master' into fusedmerge

Conflicts:
	Cython/Compiler/MemoryView.py
	Cython/Compiler/Naming.py
	Cython/Compiler/Nodes.py
	Cython/Compiler/Parsing.py
Fix error test
